name: Runners World
about: Runner's World is a globally circulated monthly magazine for runners of all skills sets, published by Hearst in Easton, Pennsylvania, in the United States.

latestReview.description: Overall, I think this magazine is "sort of" informative for runners. It will frequently focus on elite athletes or someone who has overcome an obstacle (addiction, obesity, disease) to do fantastic things. Sometimes there are fun tips, exercises, stretches, and recipes.

name: ESPN The Magazine
about: ESPN The Magazine was an American monthly sports magazine published by the ESPN sports network in Bristol, Connecticut. The first issue was published on March 11, 1998. Initially published every other week, it scaled back to 24 issues a year in early 2016, then became a monthly in its later days.

latestReview.description: ESPN magazine is a simple magazine. After reading it for a few months it is obvious their aim is to write one or two short and fun articles, then jam the rest of the magazine with random fun facts about sports.

name: Entrepreneur
about: Entrepreneur is an American magazine and website that carries news stories about entrepreneurship, small business management, and business. The magazine was first published in 1977. It is published by Entrepreneur Media Inc., headquartered in Irvine, California.

latestReview.description: If you consider yourself an entrepreneur this is the magazine for you. It's full of inspiring stories that get you up off your couch and working on your ideas. It's awesome to hear about other entrepreneurs who are doing what you want to do. Even if you are just an entrepreneur at heart this will be awesome content.

name: Travel + Leisure
about: Travel + Leisure is a travel magazine based in New York City, New York. Published 12 times a year, it has 4.8 million readers, according to its corporate media kit. It is owned and published by Travel + Leisure Co.. Its main competitor is Condé Nast Traveler.

latestReview.description: Lesson learned is dont think you know all, the level of service and feed back was amazing to the degree were my issue was escalated to ryan dewitt who setup everything that was needed not what I thought should be there.

name: The New Yorker
about: The New Yorker is an American weekly magazine featuring journalism, commentary, criticism, essays, fiction, satire, cartoons, and poetry. Started as a weekly in 1925, the magazine is now published 47 times annually, with five of these issues covering two-week spans. Although its reviews and events listings often focus on the cultural life of New York City, The New Yorker has a wide audience outside New York and is read internationally. It is well known for its illustrated and often topical covers

latestReview.description: The New Yorker magazine is known as one of the best and most prominent magazines worldwide. This magazine is popular among its readers because of its wide range of reporting, cultural explanation, political criticism, and entertainment content, including poems, fiction, comedy, e.t.c.

name: Discover
about: Discover is an American general audience science magazine launched in October 1980 by Time Inc. It has been owned by Kalmbach Publishing since 2010.

latestReview.description: Discover tells its readers about a great many subjects in the fields of science and other elements of the world we live in. It's a great window to the world far away from us and in our own homes and yards.

name: GQ
about: GQ (formerly Gentlemen's Quarterly) is an American international monthly men's magazine based in New York City and founded in 1931. The publication focuses on fashion, style, and culture for men, though articles on food, movies, fitness, sex, music, travel, sports, technology, and books are also featured.

latestReview.description: Love getting my GQ magazine home delivered each month. I love keeping up with what is going on in men's lives and minds. The clothes articles are rocking and the cover always has a hot guy on it. Ladies this is not just your mans mag its for us too!

name: AFAR
about: AFAR is a publication focused on experiential travel. The company also operates a non-profit foundation providing scholarships for educational journeys for students. Greg Sullivan and Joseph Diaz launched the magazine in 2009, after a six-week trip to India, AFAR is headquartered in San Francisco, California and has an office in New York City. The magazine was featured on The Martha Stewart Show and has received awards in the travel writing and journalism industry (Lowell Thomas Awards). Content is also available on the magazine's website and mobile application.

latestReview.description: If you love traveling, or are just wondering where to start, I think you should begin with AFAR. But be warned, once you start perusing the locales, you will want to be leaving tomorrow.

name: Baseball America
about: Baseball America is a sports magazine that covers baseball at every level, with a particular focus on up-and-coming players in high school, college, Japan, and the minor leagues. It is currently published in the form of a bi-weekly newspaper, five annual reference book titles, a weekly podcast, and a website. It also regularly produces lists of the top prospects in the sport, and covers aspects of the game from a scouting and player-development point of view. The publication's motto is Baseball news you can't find anywhere else.

latestReview.description: As a magazine, content is not interesting or insightful. A lot of space has been allocated to prospects for each MLB team... hmm. I would want to look at more MLB insight into teams, strategies, college events.

name: Cosmos
about: Cosmos is a science magazine produced in Australia with a global outlook and literary ambitions, published by the Royal Institution of Australia (RiAus). It appears four times a year in print, and browser-based subscriber editions. It has a readership of 87,000 in print, and 130,000 via browser subscribers. Its Internet sister, Cosmos Online, publishes daily news and has an audience of 400,000+ unique visitors and 1 million+ page views monthly. It is subtitled The science of everything and is described as a magazine of ideas, science, society and the future

name: Chanel
about: Chanel's combination of tradition, originality and style has always made it the most seductive of brands. Here the House of Chanel opens its private archives, revealing a galaxy of brilliant designs created by Coco Chanel from the 1920s onwards, and now reinterpreted to become the motifs for brand new garments, accessories and beauty products.

latestReview.description: Perfect to stack with other books, it’s the perfect topper to complete my nightstand. It could’ve had better packaging, there’s small indents on the exterior. It’s a decent size, weight, and beautiful!

name: Tokyo Fashion City
about: Tokyo is considered one of the world's style capitals for its vibrant youth fashion culture. Part guidebook, part fashion photography album, Tokyo Fashion City takes a stroll through eight Tokyo neighborhoods, each with its own unique fashion characteristics, to see what streetwise young Tokyoites are wearing, where they're shopping, what they're eating and drinking, and where they're hanging out.

latestReview.description: really great book, the photographs are really wonderful and I'd definitely say accurate (although this was published in 2016) its still very relevant and highlights the best of Tokyo fashion! the style of the book is very magazine-esc and reflects japanese magazine style. very useful info included, and just a delight to look through!
